## Axis discriminant construction via FromConstant

UrgencyValue / DivisibilityValue / SignificanceValue impls currently
construct their VALUE via UFixed::from_raw(N) because arvo's
FromConstant trait takes u8 and is not available at these
narrower widths. Once arvo task #123 lands (FromConstant takes
USize), revisit the three axis traits and switch to the arvo
const builder. Non-urgent; from_raw is a designated
impl-internal escape today.

## Mask256-backed AccessMask variant

Current ships with AccessMask = Mask64 (≤64 stores). A Mask256 sibling
lets pipelines address ≤256 stores at the cost of four-word bitmask
ops instead of one. Typical pipelines stay under 50 stores, so this
is a non-urgent widening. Promote when a concrete consumer exceeds 64.

## Arena runtime layout for Seq / Map

Seq<T, N> and Map<K, V, N> ship here as type-surface only. Arena
placement (stack vs co-located store arena), element layout, and
iteration contract belong to the engine round (Task #35, domain 07).
Consumers still get the const-generic type today; their runtime
location is an engine concern.

## Virtual flag bit-assignment algorithm

hilavitkutin-api carries the Virtual<T> marker and the virtual flag
surface. The plan-time assignment of virtuals to bit positions
(affinity-ordered via arvo-comb::bin_pack for hierarchical skip) is
engine-side (domain 10, Task #35).

